    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's a really constant hum like it's trying to start but just can't. and it's making this weird intermittent clicking too. does that sound like a capacitor issue or could it be something more electrical/wiring related? also i dont have a multimeter, can i tell just by looking at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A constant hum with intermittent clicking sounds could indeed be a sign of a capacitor issue, but it could also indicate a problem with the electrical wiring or other components. A faulty capacitor can cause a humming noise and may also result in clicking sounds as it struggles to start. However, it's also possible that there could be an issue with the wiring or other electrical components in the unit.\n\nWithout a multimeter, it can be challenging to diagnose the exact issue. However, you can still do a basic visual inspection. Look for any loose wires, damaged insulation, or signs of wear and tear on the wiring. Also, check if the capacitor is bulging or leaking, as this could be a sign that it's failing.\n\nIf you're not comfortable inspecting the unit or if you're unsure about anything, it's always best to call a professional. They have the necessary tools and expertise to diagnose and fix the issue safely and effectively. Remember, it's always better to be safe than sorry when it comes to electrical issues.",
